reviews.review:
Except for pace problems derived of editing and some illogical turns this is an major advance in the Disney's Trilogy, trying to undo the wrongs against the lore made in the second film and return to what the fanbase wanted.

Props for the effort.
I enjoyed the action and liked how it tied loose ends up for me.

It is a bit long but there was a lot of ground to cover. It was amazing seeing all the characters of past and present coming together (no spoiler alert here). If you have ever been a fan, you will love this movie! Bring tissues!!
Star Wars is a lifelong classic favorite. I really loved this movie because of the theme of dark turning to the light side. The characters and visual affects are second to none.

My favorite of the new trilogy! It picks up the pieces that The Last Jedi left flapping in the wind, tying them together to a satisfying end. I was engaged during the whole film too. In a lot of recent star wars films there have been scenes that seem to drag on too long, or action sequences that feel very predictable. There were star wars tropes here, but they were used sparingly and I was surprised a few times. This movie makes me like the new trilogy a lot more, planning to see it again.

Space ghosts, space ghosts and more space ghost.  Could have been better, even with space ghosts rescuing them over and over again could not help them.  It had its moments, but ugh.  I imagine in the next movie, it will be evil space ghost versus good space ghost.

The movie exists... It doesn't have anything really offensive. None of the acting feels off. The plot isn't too ridiculous for a Star Wars movie. But it doesn't really have any ideas or intellectual stimulation and it takes zero risks. As something to pass the time, it was meh. If it wasn't a Star Wars movie, I'd likely forget I even saw it.

I don't think JJ is a good match for the Star Wars franchise. He doesn't do well with plot, letting you breath, giving meaning to what s going on or allowing you to feel. Half of the movie is great, the action portion, but anything with plot or conversation is horrible.

I thought the movie was fabulous! I was constantly engaged. I've been watchign the movies in the theater since 1977 and this was as solid a Star Wars movie as they come. No funny bear costumes, no goofy sidekicks, no bad acting. A solid Star Wars adventure in the best fictional universe. I'm going to see it again.
Predictable, no build up, no real excitement. Worst Star Wars I've seen in a long time
